SIMPLE: loquacious
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Loquacious
<hw>Lo*qua"cious</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>loquax</ets>, <ets>-acis</ets>, talkative, fr. <ets>loqui</ets> to
speak; cf. Gr. <?/ to rattle, shriek, shout.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Given to continual talking; talkative; garrulous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Loquacious</qex>, brawling, ever in the wrong.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Speaking; expressive.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>J. Philips.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Apt to blab and disclose secrets.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Garrulous; talkative. See
<er>Garrulous</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Loquaciously</ent>⟦br⟧
